# Code owners for Concierge.
#
# Branch protection on `main` enforces "Require review from Code Owners"
# on any PR that touches the paths below. This is the #1 mitigation for the
# workflow-edit exfiltration attack (R1 in docs/specs/ci-signing-automation/
# plan.md) — without it, a malicious push to `main` could add a secret-
# exfiltrating step to a workflow and sign it with the repo's p12.
#
# Patterns are last-match-wins (per GitHub CODEOWNERS spec).

# Workflow files — anything that touches CI or release infra must be
# reviewed by Justin. This is the critical one for signing security.
.github/workflows/  @Jstottlemyer
.github/actions/    @Jstottlemyer

# Signing + release infra scripts (the other surface attackers would target
# if they couldn't edit workflows directly).
packages/*/build/   @Jstottlemyer

# Fallback — every other path defaults to Justin as sole maintainer.
# Remove or narrow once the project gains contributors.
*                   @Jstottlemyer
